Baseline Fleet Demand: Linear Regression Analysis

Project Scope: 2027 Machine Inflow & Install Base Workload Projection

Model Type: Ordinary Least Squares (OLS) Linear Regression

Objective: Establish a statistical "floor" for 2027 demand to compare against advanced ML models.

Methodology: The "Trend-Line" Approach
While complex models (like Random Forests) capture "spikes" and "dips," this Baseline model identifies the long-term trajectory of the fleet.

Feature Engineering: We converted categorical quarters (e.g., 2023Q4) into a continuous TIME_INDEX (e.g., 2024.0). This allows the model to calculate a mathematical slope (
) for the fleet's growth.

Target Variable (USAGE_PROXY): We utilized the historical Install Base/Fleet counts to represent the "Active Workload" that requires service support.

Model Validation (Train/Test Split)
To ensure the model isn't just "memorizing" the past, we implemented a Chronological Split:Training Set (80%): Historical data used to teach the model the growth rate.Test Set (20%): The most recent "unseen" quarters used to grade the model's accuracy.

Key Metric: The True Test MAPE (Mean Absolute Percentage Error) represents the average "miss" the model had when predicting the most recent historical quarters.

2027 Strategic Projections
The model projects four quarters into the future (2027 Q1 - Q4).

New Machine Demand: Forecasts the volume of new units entering the field.

Total Usage: Forecasts the total "Workload" (New + Existing) that the service department must be prepared to support.

